| Term                                    | Description                                                                   |
| --------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Blood Bank Management System (BBMS)** | A web-based system used to manage blood donors, inventory, and blood requests |
| **Blood Donor**                         | A registered individual who voluntarily donates blood                         |
| **Blood Inventory**                     | Records of available blood units categorized by blood group and quantity      |
| **Blood Unit**                          | A single collected and stored unit of blood                                   |
| **Blood Group**                         | Classification of blood such as A+, A−, B+, B−, O+, O−, AB+, AB−              |
| **Administrator**                       | Authorized user responsible for managing the overall system                   |
| **Hospital Staff**                      | Medical professionals who request blood for patients                          |
| **Authorized Staff**                    | Personnel responsible for updating donor and inventory data                   |
| **Blood Request**                       | A formal request for blood submitted by hospitals or authorized users         |
| **Emergency Request**                   | High-priority blood request requiring immediate processing                    |
| **Donor Eligibility**                   | Criteria determining whether a donor is allowed to donate blood               |
| **Expiration Date**                     | Date after which stored blood is no longer safe for use                       |
| **User Authentication**                 | Process of verifying user identity using login credentials                    |
| **Role-Based Access Control**           | Restriction of system features based on user roles                            |
| **Notification**                        | Alert or message sent to users regarding system events                        |
| **SRS**                                 | Software Requirements Specification document                                  |
| **UI (User Interface)**                 | Visual interface through which users interact with the system                 |
| **DBMS**                                | Database Management System used to store project data                         |
| **QA (Quality Assurance)**              | Process of ensuring system quality through testing                            |
